.SH NAME
coa-remaster - Start a system remastering flight (ISO production)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcoa remaster [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
The 'remaster' command orchestrates the creation of a bootable live ISO.
It uses the new Coala architecture to read the agnostic Brain profile
and generate a precise execution plan for the OA engine.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for remaster

.PP
\fB--mode\fP="standard"
	standard, clone, or crypted

.PP
\fB--path\fP="/home/eggs"
	working directory

.PP
\fB--stop-after\fP=""
	Ferma l'esecuzione dopo uno step specifico (es. coa-initrd)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Start a standard ISO remastering
  sudo ./coa remaster --mode standard
  
  # Debug mode: stop after a specific step
  sudo ./coa remaster --stop-after coa-initrd
.EE


